<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1616,1859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1616,1642]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from the departments of 
<collectingRegion box="[729,875,1616,1642]" country="Bolivia" name="Cochabamba" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Cochabamba</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[931,1055,1616,1642]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1092,1174,1616,1642]" name="Bolivia" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and the state of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[268,340,1652,1678]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The map is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[590,669,1652,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,866,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-41@11.[195,1392,866,1938]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 22. Distribution map of X. luctuosus (Blanchard) (white squares), X. major (Bernhauer) (star), X. max Blackwelder (black squares) and X. oliveirae Lynch (circle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6048497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6048497/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
and online at https://www.simplemappr.net/map/16397.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1616,1859]" box="[199,423,1688,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1688,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Habitat.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1616,1859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[376,474,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1906" box="[515,655,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lampropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[515,655,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">L. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from NMW agrees with the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1436,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1436,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Staphylinus luctuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined in MNHM in every respect, thus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1906" box="[632,769,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lampropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[632,769,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">L. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1142,1275,1760,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosus">
<emphasis box="[1142,1275,1760,1787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">S. luctuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The non-type male specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[383,465,1796,1822]" name="Bolivia" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
in NMW was labelled as manuscript name zischkai by Scheerpeltz, however, the specimen clearly belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[412,550,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosus">
<emphasis box="[412,550,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">X. luctuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
